default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhat is the problem?default3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultJapanese Knotweed has been a problem for landowners for years. However, more recently 
defaultthe stakes are being raised, not by legislative authorities, but by lenders
default.
default 
defaultWe have seen evidence of situations where 
defaultJapanese Knotweed 
defaulthas been
default identified at (or even in close proximity to) a property
default, and as a direct consequence
default financing 
defaulton that property has
default be
defaulten
default declined. 
defaultThis is particularly difficult for “innocent” landowners, where Japanese Knotweed is growing a neighbouring land, but has not yet encroached (see below). 
default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
